SIMPLE: phototropism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phototropism
<hw>Pho*tot"ro*pism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to turn.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Plant Physiol.)</fld> <def>The tendency of growing plant organs to
move or curve under the influence of light. In ordinary use the term is
practically synonymous with <er>heliotropism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Microbiology)</fld> <def>exhibiting movement in a
direction toward (<stype>positive phototropism</stype>) or away from
(<stype>negative phototropism</stype>) a source of light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phototype</ent>⟦br⟧
